The numbers are placed on the integer lattice in the usual “Ulam’’ square spiral:

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
\cdots&\cdots&\cdots\\
\cdots&1&\cdots\\
\end{array}
\]

The centre \(1\) is at the origin \((0,0)\); the spiral proceeds right, then up, left, down …  

---

### 1.  Coordinates of 2026  

The “layer’’ (or “ring’’) containing a number \(n\) is  

\[
k=\Bigl\lceil\frac{\sqrt n-1}{2}\Bigr\rceil .
\]

For \(n=2026\)

\[
\sqrt{2026}\approx45.011,\qquad 
k=\left\lceil\frac{45.011-1}{2}\right\rceil =23 .
\]

Hence 2026 lies on the ring \(k=23\).  
The first number of this ring is \((2k-1)^2+1 =45^{2}+1 =2026\); it is situated at  

\[
(k,\;-(k-1))=(23,\,-22).
\]

Thus the coordinates of 2026 are \((x,y)=(23,-22)\).

---

### 2.  Numbers on the eight neighbour squares  

For any lattice point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
r=\max(|x|,|y|),\qquad m=(2r+1)^2 .
\]

The maximal number on the ring \(r\) is \(m\) and it sits at \((r,-r)\).  
Going counter‑clockwise from that corner the values decrease.  
From this we obtain the following closed forms (for points on the four sides):

* bottom side (\(y=-r\)): \(N=m-(r-x)\)
* left side   (\(x=-r\)): \(N=m-(2r+(y+r))\)
* top side    (\(y=r\)): \(N=m-(4r+(x+r))\)
* right side  (\(x=r\)): \(N=m-(6r+(r-y))\)

Now evaluate the eight neighbours of \((23,-22)\).

| neighbour | \((x,y)\) | \(r\) | side | \(m\) | \(N\) |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| right            | (24,-22) | 24 | right | \(49^{2}=2401\) | \(2401-(6·24+(24-(-22))) =2401-190 = 2211\) |
| left             | (22,-22) | 22 | bottom| \(45^{2}=2025\) | \(2025-(22-22)=2025\) |
| down             | (23,-23) | 23 | bottom| \(47^{2}=2209\) | \(2209-(23-23)=2209\) |
| up               | (23,-21) | 23 | right | \(2209-(6·23+(23-(-21))) =2209-182 =2027\) |
| down‑right       | (24,-23) | 24 | right | \(2401-(6·24+(24-(-23))) =2401-191 =2210\) |
| up‑right         | (24,-21) | 24 | right | \(2401-(6·24+(24-(-21))) =2401-189 =2212\) |
| down‑left        | (22,-23) | 23 | bottom| \(2209-(23-22)=2208\) |
| up‑left          | (22,-21) | 22 | right | \(2025-(6·22+(22-(-21))) =2025-175 =1850\) |

---

### 3.  Sum of the eight neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum}&=
2211+2025+2209+2027+2210+2212+2208+1850 \\
&= 16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
